# PIVOTEX — .gitignore
#
# By default we keep the brain structure tracked but exclude personal/runtime data.
# Adjust as needed for your fork: many users WILL want to commit their hippocampus
# entries for backup; others will not. Tune to taste.

# === Personal user data (filled in during onboarding) ===
# Uncomment to keep limbic/user.md out of version control once filled in:
# limbic/user.md

# === Runtime/personal content ===
# Daily hippocampus entries (dated YYYY-MM-DD.md). Not tracked by default.
hippocampus/2*.md
!hippocampus/_template.md
!hippocampus/_last7days.md

# Hippocampus archives (long-term local-only by default)
hippocampus/archive/

# Personal source documents — your private inputs
sources/*
!sources/_index.md
!sources/.gitkeep

# Speculative dreams — local-only by default
dreams/*
!dreams/_index.md
!dreams/.gitkeep

# Forgotten archive
archive/

# === OS / editor cruft ===
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini
*.swp
*.swo
*~
.vscode/
.idea/

# === Sandboxes from test runs (kept under temp normally, but just in case) ===
**/cortex-test-*/
**/pivotex-test-*/
